{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Grease 12 mini loose-base tartlet tins (3.5 cm base) or 24 mini silicone mini muffin cases with butter.","Place almonds, buckwheat groats and sage into mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add butter, salt, 10 g of the walnuts and 10 g of the dried pear and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Press 1 teaspoon of the mixture into the base of each tartlet tin or silicone mini muffin case. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place cream cheese, Gorgonzola, egg, lemon juice and remaining 60 g walnuts into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Spoon 1½ teaspoons of the mixture into each mould over base mixture and bake for 15 minutes (160°C) or until filling is set. Transfer onto a wire rack to cool before removing from tins or moulds. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place remaining 70 g dried pears into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add vinegar, water, sugar and pepper and cook <b>5-8 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>, until thick and sticky. Top each cheesecake with ½ teaspoon of the pear jam and garnish with thyme leaves to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["60 g unsalted butter, plus extra for greasing","10 g blanched almonds","20 g buckwheat groats","1 sprig fresh sage, leaves only","1 pinch salt","70 g walnuts","80 g dried pear","100 g cream cheese","120 g Gorgonzola cheese (dolce or soft)","1 egg","1 tsp lemon juice","45 g balsamic vinegar","40 g water","25 g brown sugar","1 pinch ground black pepper","fresh thyme leaves, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r277392","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-GZ0WQ61Ki4E\/XZMvz3Ul71I\/AAAAAAAAaWc\/aWmM29Z9r00wFLNAfYXfqJdlqJYs32B6gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_q44k_83XG4Yv04Gu.png","title":"Gorgonzola cheesecakes with pear jam","publishedAt":"2018-05-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.9 g","fat":"15.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"6.8 g","calories":"786.5 kJ \/ 187.3 kcal"},